I GOT THINGS TO DO TODAY.

09:27.734 --> 09:30.529
SO I'M ONLY GONNA SAY THIS ONCE.

09:30.529 --> 09:32.864
THIS IS

09:30.529 --> 09:32.864
A CARBON DIOXIDE MONITOR.

09:32.864 --> 09:34.449
DOES ANYBODY IN HERE

09:32.864 --> 09:34.449
KNOW WHAT THAT DOES?

09:34.449 --> 09:35.909
-IT MEASURES --

09:34.449 --> 09:35.909
-WRONG.

09:35.909 --> 09:38.453
IT  MONITORS  CARBON DIOXIDE.

09:38.453 --> 09:40.163
THERE'S ONE IN EVERY SINGLE ROOM

09:38.453 --> 09:40.163
IN THE WINERY,

09:40.163 --> 09:43.375
JUST LIKE THE ONE

09:40.163 --> 09:43.375
ON THE WALL BACK THERE.

09:43.375 --> 09:47.754
THIS READS OUT

09:43.375 --> 09:47.754
REAL-TIME CO2 LEVELS.

09:47.754 --> 09:50.215
AND...NONE OF YOU KNOW

09:47.754 --> 09:50.215
WHAT THAT MEANS.

09:50.215 --> 09:52.300
OKAY. YOU.

09:52.300 --> 09:54.553
YOU'RE ON SUPPLIES.

09:52.300 --> 09:54.553
GET ME EVERYTHING ON THIS LIST.

09:54.553 --> 09:56.721
I MEAN, EVERYTHING.

09:54.553 --> 09:56.721
IT'S GONNA TAKE YOU A WHILE.

09:56.721 --> 09:59.015
YOU GET IT?

09:56.721 --> 09:59.015
YOU -- YOU SEE WHAT I'M SAYING?

09:59.015 --> 10:01.435
AYE-AYE, CAPTAIN.

10:03.437 --> 10:05.021
WHAT Y'ALL STANDING AROUND

10:03.437 --> 10:05.021
LOOKING AT ME FOR?

10:05.021 --> 10:06.481
I SEE A ROOM FULL OF SMUDGES

10:06.481 --> 10:08.024
AND A BUNCH OF PEOPLE

10:06.481 --> 10:08.024
WITH BROOMS AND MOPS.

10:08.024 --> 10:10.318
GET TO IT.

10:10.318 --> 10:11.945
I DON'T HAVE A MOP IN MY HAND.

10:11.945 --> 10:14.322
I CAN'T DO NOTHING ABOUT IT.

10:11.945 --> 10:14.322
CAN'T HELP YOU. I'M SORRY.

10:14.322 --> 10:17.158
[ CHUCKLES ]

10:17.158 --> 10:19.160
AGE OF THE GEEK, BABY.

10:19.160 --> 10:22.414
I AM THE GRAPE GATSBY.

10:22.414 --> 10:25.584
[ SIGHS ]

10:22.414 --> 10:25.584
CAN'T TAKE THIS ANYMORE.

10:25.584 --> 10:26.918
CLEAN, CLEAN, CLEAN.

10:26.918 --> 10:29.087
INTERNS DO THIS,

10:26.918 --> 10:29.087
INTERNS DO THAT.

10:29.087 --> 10:30.630
YOU KNOW WHAT?

10:30.630 --> 10:33.383
I DON'T THINK THIS  IS

10:30.630 --> 10:33.383
A VALUABLE WORK EXPERIENCE.

10:33.383 --> 10:36.303
YOU GOT A LITTLE SOMETHING

10:33.383 --> 10:36.303
ON YOU RIGHT THERE.

10:36.303 --> 10:38.012
LOOK.

10:38.012 --> 10:39.139
I DON'T KNOW HOW MUCH...

10:39.139 --> 10:41.808
-WHO'S THAT?

10:39.139 --> 10:41.808
-HIS NAME'S LEONARD.

10:41.808 --> 10:43.435
IT'S MADIGAN'S RIGHT-HAND GUY.

10:43.435 --> 10:47.188
HE'S GOT A VERY

10:43.435 --> 10:47.188
PUNCHABLE FACE.

10:47.188 --> 10:50.525
YEAH, I NOTICED THAT.

10:53.945 --> 10:55.738
OKAY, IT'S TIME TO GET YOU IN.

10:55.738 --> 10:57.198
-HERE'S WHAT I'M THINKING.

10:55.738 --> 10:57.198
-OH, NO.

10:57.198 --> 10:58.741
I'M GONNA THINK

10:57.198 --> 10:58.741
OF SOMETHING FUN.

10:58.741 --> 11:01.661
THIS ISN'T MY FIRST PICNIC

10:58.741 --> 11:01.661
WITH A WINE COLLECTOR.

11:01.661 --> 11:04.080
I KNOW, SOPHIE,

11:01.661 --> 11:04.080
BUT YOU HAVE TO BE CAREFUL.

11:04.080 --> 11:05.415
THIS IS SOMEONE WHO KNOWS

11:04.080 --> 11:05.415
HOW TO MAKE WINE

11:05.415 --> 11:07.125
ON A MOLECULAR LEVEL.

11:07.125 --> 11:09.628
OKAY? THIS ISN'T SOME, YOU KNOW,

11:07.125 --> 11:09.628
RICH PERSON'S WEEKEND HOBBY.

11:09.628 --> 11:11.754
YOU CAN'T FOOL A SCIENTIST

11:09.628 --> 11:11.754
AT HIS BUSINESS.

11:11.754 --> 11:14.007
IT'S JUST ABOUT STATUS.

11:14.007 --> 11:15.758
WINE'S JUST ANOTHER WAY

11:14.007 --> 11:15.758
OF SAYING,

11:15.758 --> 11:17.051
"I'M BETTER. I BELONG."

11:17.051 --> 11:18.637
AND THAT'S  MY  BUSINESS.

11:18.637 --> 11:21.097
EH, END OF THE DAY,

11:18.637 --> 11:21.097
SOME THINGS CAN'T BE FAKED.

11:21.097 --> 11:24.434
END OF THE DAY, THERE'S FAKE...

11:24.434 --> 11:27.270
and then there's fake.

11:27.270 --> 11:30.398
I'D LIKE TO KNOW THE DIFFERENCE.

11:33.401 --> 11:35.570
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

11:38.365 --> 11:41.075
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

11:41.075 --> 11:45.079
OH, THANK YOU SO MUCH. ENJOY.

11:48.749 --> 11:51.836
-MR. MADIGAN. CHANTALE MITCHELL.

11:48.749 --> 11:51.836
-HMM?

11:51.836 --> 11:54.172
YOU'RE LOOKING FOR A NEW POURER?

11:54.172 --> 11:55.632
H.R. HANDLES THOSE APPLICATIONS.

11:55.632 --> 11:57.634
OH, I'M NOT ONE

11:55.632 --> 11:57.634
FOR FILLING OUT FORMS.

11:57.634 --> 11:59.511
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT,

11:57.634 --> 11:59.511
MR. MADIGAN.

11:59.511 --> 12:01.638
I SELL A CASE OF WINE --

12:01.638 --> 12:03.557
A CASE OF WINE TO ANY CUSTOMER

12:01.638 --> 12:03.557
IN THIS ROOM --

12:03.557 --> 12:05.141
I'M YOUR GIRL.

12:05.141 --> 12:06.976
YOU'LL NEVER LAND THEM.

12:05.141 --> 12:06.976
THESE PEOPLE ARE LOOKY-LOOS.

12:06.976 --> 12:09.229
THEY'RE HERE BECAUSE

12:06.976 --> 12:09.229
THE TASTING IS FREE.

12:09.229 --> 12:10.938
EXCUSE ME.

12:10.938 --> 12:12.815
MR. MADIGAN.

12:13.858 --> 12:18.154
I AM VERY, VERY PERSUASIVE.

12:20.073 --> 12:23.159
ALL RIGHT, THEN.

12:23.159 --> 12:27.205
LET'S START WITH

12:23.159 --> 12:27.205
THE TOUGHEST CUSTOMER HERE.

12:27.205 --> 12:30.208
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

12:30.208 --> 12:31.834
WHAT ARE WE LOOKING FOR, NATE?

12:31.834 --> 12:33.961
Okay, the most common cause

12:31.834 --> 12:33.961
of death for field workers

12:33.961 --> 12:36.339
ARE DEHYDRATION AND HYPOTHERMIA.

12:36.339 --> 12:38.258
WELL, SO MUCH FOR DEHYDRATION.

12:38.258 --> 12:40.468
IT'S BEEN WARM HERE

12:38.258 --> 12:40.468
FOR OVER THREE WEEKS.

12:40.468 --> 12:41.802
NO ONE'S FREEZING TO DEATH.

12:41.802 --> 12:44.138
BREAK'S OVER!

12:44.138 --> 12:46.600
BACK TO WORK!

12:46.600 --> 12:50.228
[ SIGHS ]

12:46.600 --> 12:50.228
I DO NOT LIKE THAT GUY.

12:50.228 --> 12:52.606
NATE, THIS GUY WORKS

12:50.228 --> 12:52.606
EVERYBODY REALLY HARD,

12:52.606 --> 12:54.274
BUT HE'S NOT KILLING ANYONE.

12:54.274 --> 12:56.526
If Madigan was willing

12:54.274 --> 12:56.526
to pay through the nose

12:56.526 --> 13:00.739
to cover up Sam's death --

12:56.526 --> 13:00.739
keep looking.

13:00.739 --> 13:03.199
YOU LIKE THE FINER THINGS.

13:03.199 --> 13:06.077
AND YOU'RE NOT AFRAID

13:03.199 --> 13:06.077
TO SHOW IT.

13:06.077 --> 13:07.995
YOU'RE A CAB MAN.

13:09.997 --> 13:12.250
CUT THE SMALL TALK AND POUR.

13:12.250 --> 13:15.503
IT'S OUR 2010. BIG FLAVORS.

13:15.503 --> 13:16.755
IT'S JAMMY.

13:16.755 --> 13:20.216
TASTE THE NOTES

13:16.755 --> 13:20.216
OF BLACK CURRANT.

13:20.216 --> 13:22.385
[ SNIFFS ]

13:24.803 --> 13:27.307
IT'S FINE, BUT I'M NOT REACHING

13:24.803 --> 13:27.307
FOR MY WALLET.

13:27.307 --> 13:31.394
LET'S TRY SOMETHING DIFFERENT.

13:27.307 --> 13:31.394
SOMETHING SPECIAL.

13:31.394 --> 13:32.895
I KNOW THE WINES, LADY.

13:32.895 --> 13:35.482
NEXT TIME DON'T TRY

13:32.895 --> 13:35.482
TO SNOW THE BOSS.

13:35.482 --> 13:38.859
THE VINTNER USUALLY HOLDS BACK

13:35.482 --> 13:38.859
SOMETHING NICE FOR THE STAFF.

13:38.859 --> 13:40.027
AH!

13:40.027 --> 13:42.280
WHAT IS IT?

13:42.280 --> 13:45.408
NO PEEKING.

13:46.785 --> 13:48.827
THE FINER THINGS...

13:48.827 --> 13:52.624
FOR A FINE WINE.

14:02.133 --> 14:05.720
BETTER, RIGHT?

14:02.133 --> 14:05.720
STRUCTURED, SUPPLE.

14:05.720 --> 14:09.599
TASTES LIKE MONEY.

14:05.720 --> 14:09.599
WHAT IS IT, THE '08?

14:10.558 --> 14:12.893
IT'S STILL THE 2010.

14:12.893 --> 14:16.189
WAIT. THE SAME WINE.

14:16.189 --> 14:17.148
I TASTED THE DIFFERENCE.

14:17.148 --> 14:18.191
NO.

14:18.191 --> 14:20.067
YOU EXPECTED THE SECOND GLASS

14:20.067 --> 14:22.153
TO TASTE BETTER

14:20.067 --> 14:22.153
THAN THE FIRST GLASS.

14:22.153 --> 14:24.113
I TOLD YOU A STORY.

14:24.113 --> 14:26.032
I SET THE TABLE.

14:26.032 --> 14:28.827
YOU TASTED WHAT YOU WANTED

14:26.032 --> 14:28.827
TO TASTE.

14:28.827 --> 14:31.329
THAT'S DISTURBING.

14:36.459 --> 14:37.669
THE FAMILY THAT OWNED THIS PLACE

14:37.669 --> 14:39.295
DIDN'T CARE

14:37.669 --> 14:39.295
IF THEY TURNED A PROFIT,

14:39.295 --> 14:40.963
SO LONG AS THEY MADE

14:39.295 --> 14:40.963
A BETTER BOTTLE.

14:40.963 --> 14:42.882
THEY MADE 20,000 CASES A YEAR.

14:42.882 --> 14:44.592
YOU KNOW WHAT I CALL THAT?

14:44.592 --> 14:46.177
SMALL-TIME.

14:46.177 --> 14:49.347
I'M MAKING BIG CHANGES.

14:46.177 --> 14:49.347
200,000 CASES A YEAR.

14:49.347 --> 14:52.058
THE WINE WILL COST ME

14:49.347 --> 14:52.058
HALF AS MUCH TO MAKE.

14:52.058 --> 14:54.894
WON'T TASTE THE SAME,

14:52.058 --> 14:54.894
BUT IT'LL BE GOOD ENOUGH.

14:54.894 --> 14:58.939
I NEED SOMEONE

14:54.894 --> 14:58.939
WHO CAN HELP ME SELL IT.

14:58.939 --> 15:01.108
YOU ON BOARD?

15:03.027 --> 15:05.530
OF COURSE, MR. MADIGAN.

15:08.616 --> 15:12.453
LOOK FOR ENDOSULFANS

15:08.616 --> 15:12.453
AND ORGANOCHLORINES.

15:12.453 --> 15:14.581
THEY'RE ILLEGAL PESTICIDES --

15:12.453 --> 15:14.581
COULD HAVE KILLED OUR VICTIM.

15:14.581 --> 15:17.958
THIS VOCABULARY

15:14.581 --> 15:17.958
IS NOT THIEF-FRIENDLY.

15:17.958 --> 15:20.628
JUST SCAN AND MOVE ON.

15:20.628 --> 15:23.423
CLEAR. IT'S FERTILIZER.

15:25.592 --> 15:27.552
SOMEONE CHANGED THE LABELS.

15:27.552 --> 15:30.388
-IT'S NOT FERTILIZER.

15:27.552 --> 15:30.388
-THEN WHAT IS IT?

15:32.682 --> 15:35.810
DON'T GET IT ON YOUR HANDS.

15:35.810 --> 15:37.729
THAT'S IT, ELIOT -- PROOF.

15:37.729 --> 15:39.439
MAYBE.

15:37.729 --> 15:39.439
WE GOT SOMETHING, NATE.

15:39.439 --> 15:41.148
YEAH, HUNDREDS OF GALLONS

15:39.439 --> 15:41.148
OF SOMETHING.

15:41.148 --> 15:42.358
We got a sample.

15:42.358 --> 15:43.818
GET IT TO HARDISON.

15:42.358 --> 15:43.818
I WANT IT I.D.'d.

15:43.818 --> 15:45.278
HUNDREDS OF GALLONS --

15:45.278 --> 15:47.321
THAT MEANS THERE'S

15:45.278 --> 15:47.321
PURCHASE ORDERS, USAGE LOGS.

15:47.321 --> 15:49.574
WE NEED EVIDENCE THAT'S

15:47.321 --> 15:49.574
GONNA HOLD UP IN COURT.

15:49.574 --> 15:51.033
PARKER, FIND THE PAPER TRAIL.

15:51.033 --> 15:52.993
COULD BE POISON.

15:54.913 --> 15:56.205
CAN'T LET THEM USE THIS.

15:56.205 --> 15:58.792
YOU GO. I'LL TAKE CARE OF IT.

15:59.834 --> 16:01.669
OKAY, HARDISON, SOPHIE,

15:59.834 --> 16:01.669
START THE CON.

16:01.669 --> 16:03.671
KEEP IT SIMPLE.

16:01.669 --> 16:03.671
A SWAP-AND-WHISPER CAMPAIGN.

16:03.671 --> 16:06.591
SOPHIE, I BET

16:03.671 --> 16:06.591
YOU'RE HALFWAY THERE.

16:06.591 --> 16:09.343
3/4.

16:06.591 --> 16:09.343
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

16:09.343 --> 16:10.929
HEY, NATE, I THINK I'M MAKING

16:10.929 --> 16:12.889
QUITE AN IMPRESSION

16:10.929 --> 16:12.889
ON OUR MARK.

16:12.889 --> 16:14.974
-ENJOY.

16:12.889 --> 16:14.974
-HEY.

16:14.974 --> 16:16.183
PINOT SOLD OUT.

16:16.183 --> 16:17.977
SO DID THE SYRAH

16:16.183 --> 16:17.977
AND THE CHARDONNAY.

16:17.977 --> 16:20.396
PRE-ORDERS FOR NEXT YEAR

16:17.977 --> 16:20.396
ARE THROUGH THE ROOF.

16:20.396 --> 16:21.940
LET'S CELEBRATE.

16:21.940 --> 16:23.650
[ SIGHS ] I'M DYING FOR A DRINK.

16:21.940 --> 16:23.650
AND THE GOOD STUFF.

16:23.650 --> 16:25.735
I'VE HEARD AMAZING THINGS

16:23.650 --> 16:25.735
ABOUT YOUR COLLECTION.

16:25.735 --> 16:26.903
I GOT A COUPLE OF BOTTLES

16:26.903 --> 16:28.321
I'VE BEEN SAVING

16:26.903 --> 16:28.321
FOR THE RIGHT TIME.

16:28.321 --> 16:31.282
I GOT JUST THE PLACE

16:28.321 --> 16:31.282
FOR A DRINK. COME ON.

16:31.282 --> 16:34.494
OH.

16:37.371 --> 16:40.583
TOWER'S MY FAVORITE PART

16:37.371 --> 16:40.583
OF THE WHOLE BUILDING.

16:40.583 --> 16:42.669
HMM. IT'S GORGEOUS.

16:42.669 --> 16:44.504
IS IT PART OF

16:42.669 --> 16:44.504
THE ORIGINAL WINERY?

16:44.504 --> 16:47.006
YEAH, SEE,

16:47.006 --> 16:51.135
AT HARVEST, CARBON DIOXIDE

16:47.006 --> 16:51.135
BUILDS UP AROUND THE TANKS.

16:51.135 --> 16:54.555
HUNDREDS OF TONS OF GRAPES

16:51.135 --> 16:54.555
AND YEAST-MAKING ALCOHOL

16:54.555 --> 16:55.807
RELEASING CO2.

16:55.807 --> 16:58.476
YOU CAN'T SEE IT, SMELL IT.

16:58.476 --> 17:02.772
YOU JUST FEEL A BIT WOOZY,

16:58.476 --> 17:02.772
AND THEN...

17:02.772 --> 17:04.023
YOU'RE DONE.

17:04.023 --> 17:05.692
OOH. SCARY.

17:05.692 --> 17:08.486
YEAH, WELL, NOWADAYS, WE USE

17:05.692 --> 17:08.486
AIR MOVERS AND HVAC SYSTEMS

17:08.486 --> 17:10.655
TO KEEP THE LEVELS DOWN.

17:08.486 --> 17:10.655
BUT IN THE OLD DAYS,

17:10.655 --> 17:13.658
THESE DOORS WOULD OPEN UP

17:10.655 --> 17:13.658
AND FLUSH THE WHOLE WINERY

17:13.658 --> 17:14.742
WITH FRESH AIR.

17:14.742 --> 17:16.953
-IT'S PRETTY IMPRESSIVE.

17:14.742 --> 17:16.953
-WELL...

17:16.953 --> 17:18.705
IT'S LIKE THE PLACE

17:16.953 --> 17:18.705
WHEN I BOUGHT IT.

17:18.705 --> 17:20.999
IT'S GOOD FOR ITS TIME.

17:20.999 --> 17:23.459
BUT TIMES CHANGE,

17:20.999 --> 17:23.459
SCIENCE MARCHES ON.

17:23.459 --> 17:25.712
-WHAT DO YOU THINK OF THE WINE?

17:23.459 --> 17:25.712
-MM.

17:25.712 --> 17:27.714
IT'S GOOD.

17:27.714 --> 17:30.257
BUT I UNDERSTOOD YOU HAD

17:27.714 --> 17:30.257
SOME REALLY RARE BOTTLES.

17:30.257 --> 17:33.511
YEAH. YOU WANT TO SEE MY CAVE?

17:33.511 --> 17:36.138
TRY AND STOP ME.

17:36.138 --> 17:37.473
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:43.521 --> 17:47.191
AND YOUR BUTTON CAM

17:43.521 --> 17:47.191
IS NOW ONLINE.

17:47.191 --> 17:49.443
OKAY, ALL RIGHT, SOPHIE,

17:47.191 --> 17:49.443
GET READY TO SWAP.

17:49.443 --> 17:51.029
KILLING THE LIGHTS

17:49.443 --> 17:51.029
AT YOUR SAY-SO.

17:51.029 --> 17:52.363
WOW.

17:52.363 --> 17:53.656
NICE, HUH?

17:53.656 --> 17:56.743
I PULLED SOME OF

17:53.656 --> 17:56.743
MY FAVORITE BOTTLES.

17:56.743 --> 17:59.871
[ SIGHS ]

17:59.871 --> 18:02.540
AH. [ GASPS ]

18:02.540 --> 18:05.376
BELLA NUNZIO.

18:02.540 --> 18:05.376
RION DES LANDES.

18:05.376 --> 18:07.670
MM.

18:07.670 --> 18:11.799
1934 CHATEAU MARGAUX.

18:11.799 --> 18:13.426
FRANK...

18:28.733 --> 18:30.651
OWNED BY THOMAS JEFFERSON

18:28.733 --> 18:30.651
HIMSELF.

18:30.651 --> 18:33.947
ISN'T THAT SOMETHING?

18:30.651 --> 18:33.947
OVER 200 YEARS OLD?

18:33.947 --> 18:35.865
I PUT SOME SERIOUS SECURITY

18:33.947 --> 18:35.865
ON THIS THING.

18:35.865 --> 18:38.618
OH. MAY I?

18:40.661 --> 18:43.372
IT'S GOT ITS OWN UNIQUE

18:40.661 --> 18:43.372
I.D. NUMBER.

18:43.372 --> 18:45.708
YOU CAN'T OPEN IT

18:43.372 --> 18:45.708
WITHOUT BREAKING THE SEAL.

18:45.708 --> 18:48.002
NO ONE CAN SWAP IT OUT

18:45.708 --> 18:48.002
WITHOUT ME KNOWING.

18:48.002 --> 18:49.963
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

18:48.002 --> 18:49.963
HANG ON. HANG ON.

18:51.338 --> 18:54.341
YOU PUT A LICENSE PLATE

18:51.338 --> 18:54.341
ON YOUR WINE.

18:54.341 --> 18:56.427
COME ON. HE PUT A LICENSE PLATE

18:54.341 --> 18:56.427
ON THE WINE?

18:56.427 --> 18:58.012
WHO DOES THAT?

18:58.012 --> 18:59.639
THIS IS -- THIS IS GONNA TAKE

18:58.012 --> 18:59.639
DAYS FOR ME TO CRACK.

18:59.639 --> 19:01.307
AND BY THE TIME I DO,

18:59.639 --> 19:01.307
THERE'S NO GUARANTEE

19:01.307 --> 19:03.101
THAT SOPHIE CAN GET BACK

19:01.307 --> 19:03.101
IN THAT WINE CELLAR.

19:03.101 --> 19:06.186
PLUS, WE DON'T WANT THE WORKERS

19:03.101 --> 19:06.186
BREATHING THIS STUFF IN ANYMORE.

19:06.186 --> 19:07.438
MADIGAN HAS TO BE CAUGHT

19:07.438 --> 19:09.398
WITH A FRAUDULENT

19:07.438 --> 19:09.398
WINE COLLECTION, OKAY?

19:09.398 --> 19:11.818
AND HOW DO WE DO THAT

19:09.398 --> 19:11.818
IF WE CAN'T SWAP BOTTLES?

19:11.818 --> 19:14.278
JUST MAKE THE REAL BOTTLE

19:11.818 --> 19:14.278
LOOK FAKE.

19:14.278 --> 19:17.281
A 200-YEAR-OLD BOTTLE

19:14.278 --> 19:17.281
THAT WE CAN'T SWAP -- HOW?

19:17.281 --> 19:20.076
EH, I'M WORKING ON IT.

19:17.281 --> 19:20.076
OKAY, PARKER?

19:20.076 --> 19:21.911
About that paper trail --

19:20.076 --> 19:21.911
go find it.

19:21.911 --> 19:23.537
GREAT. GOT TO FORGE A BOTTLE.

19:23.537 --> 19:26.206
TEST THE MYSTERY FLUID

19:23.537 --> 19:26.206
AND FORGE A BOTTLE.

19:26.206 --> 19:27.959
EASY DAY. YAY.

19:27.959 --> 19:30.294
NOW, SOPHIE,

19:27.959 --> 19:30.294
START THE WHISPER CAMPAIGN.

19:30.294 --> 19:31.879
MAKE HIM DOUBT HIS OWN BOTTLE.

19:31.879 --> 19:35.215
HUH.

19:35.215 --> 19:36.843
WOW.

19:36.843 --> 19:40.013
THAT PONSOT LOOKS TO DIE FOR.

19:40.013 --> 19:41.973
DID YOU JUST SAY "HUH"

