30:21.903 --> 30:23.905
AS QUICKLY AS POSSIBLE.

30:23.905 --> 30:25.073
PAUL. GIVE ME YOUR HAT.

30:25.073 --> 30:26.450
I NEED YOUR HAT

30:25.073 --> 30:26.450
AND YOUR JACKET.

30:26.450 --> 30:27.826
-QUICK. QUICK.

30:26.450 --> 30:27.826
-NO PROBLEM.

30:27.826 --> 30:28.827
JUST TAKE IT OFF QUICK.

30:28.827 --> 30:30.496
WE'LL FIND HER.

30:30.496 --> 30:31.830
[ PANTING ]

30:31.830 --> 30:33.666
THAT'S HER. LET'S GO.

30:42.591 --> 30:45.344
AND NOW FOR THE GEIGER COUNTER.

30:45.344 --> 30:47.179
OKAY, GUYS,

30:45.344 --> 30:47.179
SO, HERE'S THE THING.

30:47.179 --> 30:48.430
ALL WINE BOTTLED AFTER 1947

30:48.430 --> 30:50.307
HAVE TRACE AMOUNTS

30:48.430 --> 30:50.307
OF RADIOACTIVITY.

30:50.307 --> 30:54.186
Cesium isotopes from

30:50.307 --> 30:54.186
atmospheric nuclear testing.

30:54.186 --> 30:56.938
WHERE DID YOU GET

30:54.186 --> 30:56.938
RADIOACTIVE CESIUM?

30:56.938 --> 31:00.442
THE THINGS I DO FOR NATE.

31:00.442 --> 31:02.611
[ ALARMS BLARING ]

31:06.865 --> 31:08.867
[ SIGHS ]

31:06.865 --> 31:08.867
[ DOGS BARKING ]

31:08.867 --> 31:11.870
[ GROANS ]

31:11.870 --> 31:14.956
WAIT -- SO IF IT'S RADIOACTIVE,

31:11.870 --> 31:14.956
THEN WHY ARE WE DRINKING IT?

31:14.956 --> 31:16.667
OH, COME ON, NOW, IT'S SAFE.

31:16.667 --> 31:18.585
THERE ARE TRACE AMOUNTS

31:16.667 --> 31:18.585
OF CESIUM EVERYWHERE --

31:18.585 --> 31:20.713
ON YOU, ON ME --

31:18.585 --> 31:20.713
EVERYWHERE BUT OLD WINE.

31:20.713 --> 31:23.507
WHICH IS WHY HARDISON DIPPED

31:20.713 --> 31:23.507
THE AUDITOR'S GLOVES

31:23.507 --> 31:25.925
INTO A SLURRY CONTAINING

31:23.507 --> 31:25.925
THE ISOTOPE.

31:34.142 --> 31:37.563
SO I'M RADIOACTIVE?

31:34.142 --> 31:37.563
WHY DON'T I HAVE SUPERPOWERS?

31:37.563 --> 31:39.773
BABE, WE ALL FEEL CHEATED.

31:39.773 --> 31:42.150
[ CLICKING ]

31:42.150 --> 31:44.403
MORE CLICKS IS GOOD, RIGHT?

31:48.281 --> 31:49.991
ALL RIGHT. NOT BAD.

31:49.991 --> 31:52.285
NOW, YOU'VE TAKEN THE OLDEST

31:49.991 --> 31:52.285
BOTTLE OF WINE I'VE EVER SEEN

31:52.285 --> 31:54.663
AND MADE IT LOOK UNDERAGE --

31:52.285 --> 31:54.663
PRETTY GOOD.

31:54.663 --> 31:56.915
HE'LL TELL THE BANK IMMEDIATELY.

31:56.915 --> 32:00.794
MADIGAN...

31:56.915 --> 32:00.794
KISS YOUR WINERY GOODBYE.

32:00.794 --> 32:02.504
WAIT FOR IT.

32:03.756 --> 32:06.592
GENUINE.

32:06.592 --> 32:08.510
-WHAT?

32:08.510 --> 32:09.969
CONGRATULATIONS, SIR.

32:11.847 --> 32:14.307
HOW...

32:14.307 --> 32:16.226
[ OBJECT CLATTERS ]

32:14.307 --> 32:16.226
DAMN IT.

32:16.226 --> 32:19.229
[ SIGHS ] HE IS NOWHERE NEAR

32:16.226 --> 32:19.229
LOSING THIS WINERY.

32:19.229 --> 32:21.273
NO. NO, HE ISN'T.

32:21.273 --> 32:24.526
BOTTLE FAILED EVERY SINGLE TEST.

32:21.273 --> 32:24.526
HOW'S THAT POSSIBLE?

32:24.526 --> 32:27.237
NATE.

32:27.237 --> 32:30.156
I TRACKED BETTY.

32:32.367 --> 32:34.327
I GOT FOOTPRINTS HERE.

32:34.327 --> 32:37.997
Leonard's guys got to her first.

32:34.327 --> 32:37.997
Three guys.

32:37.997 --> 32:40.333
SHE PUT UP A STRUGGLE.

32:41.877 --> 32:43.796
THEY'VE TAKEN HER, NATE.

32:43.796 --> 32:46.715
We've been shaking

32:43.796 --> 32:46.715
things up a bit.

32:46.715 --> 32:49.134
WE PUT MADIGAN ON BETTY'S TRAIL.

32:49.134 --> 32:51.177
Okay, Eliot, get her back.

32:51.177 --> 32:53.513
YEP.

32:53.513 --> 32:54.848
WE SUCCEEDED TOO WELL.

32:54.848 --> 32:56.809
WE DIDN'T JUST MAKE HIM

32:54.848 --> 32:56.809
DOUBT THE WINE.

32:56.809 --> 33:01.521
WE CONVINCED HIM IT WAS FAKE.

32:56.809 --> 33:01.521
SO HE BRIBED THE AUDITOR.

33:01.521 --> 33:02.773
HEY!

33:02.773 --> 33:05.066
THE BOTTLE IS REAL!

33:02.773 --> 33:05.066
THAT'S AMAZING.

33:05.066 --> 33:06.151
LET'S CELEBRATE.

33:06.151 --> 33:08.153
I'M IN THE MIDDLE

33:06.151 --> 33:08.153
OF SOMETHING.

33:08.153 --> 33:09.696
WHAT? NO.

33:09.696 --> 33:12.073
WHAT COULD BE

33:09.696 --> 33:12.073
MORE IMPORTANT?

33:12.073 --> 33:14.952
TAKE THE DAY OFF.

33:12.073 --> 33:14.952
WE'RE CLOSING EARLY.

33:14.952 --> 33:17.621
WHAT ABOUT YOU?

33:18.747 --> 33:21.708
I SAID GO HOME.

33:25.211 --> 33:27.673
NATE.

33:27.673 --> 33:30.425
MADIGAN'S GIVING EVERYONE

33:27.673 --> 33:30.425
A VACATION DAY.

33:30.425 --> 33:32.385
Something's going down

33:30.425 --> 33:32.385
at the winery.

33:32.385 --> 33:36.473
HIS WINE COLLECTION IS SAFE.

33:32.385 --> 33:36.473
HIS LOAN IS SAFE.

33:36.473 --> 33:38.308
WHAT IS HE UP TO?

33:38.308 --> 33:41.144
NATE, SOMETHING'S UP.

33:38.308 --> 33:41.144
IT'S THE CO2 MONITORS.

33:41.144 --> 33:45.732
THIS IS THE WINERY APP I MADE.

33:41.144 --> 33:45.732
LETS ME ACCESS MY WORKSTATION.

33:45.732 --> 33:47.442
ALL THE CO2 MONITORS

33:45.732 --> 33:47.442
ARE OFFLINE.

33:47.442 --> 33:49.611
SO MADIGAN'S ABOUT TO MANIPULATE

33:47.442 --> 33:49.611
THE CARBON DIOXIDE LEVELS.

33:49.611 --> 33:51.154
I'D SAY HE'S PROBABLY

33:49.611 --> 33:51.154
GOING FOR SOMEWHERE

33:51.154 --> 33:52.823
BETWEEN DEADLY AND LETHAL.

33:52.823 --> 33:55.701
HE JUST CLOSED DOWN THE WINERY.

33:52.823 --> 33:55.701
WHO IS HE TRYING TO HURT?

33:55.701 --> 33:58.871
YOUR MISSING WORKER. YEAH.

33:58.871 --> 34:00.539
IF I WERE MADIGAN,

33:58.871 --> 34:00.539
I'D MAKE IT LOOK LIKE

34:00.539 --> 34:02.875
BETTY CARTER TAMPERED

34:00.539 --> 34:02.875
WITH THOSE CO2 MONITORS

34:02.875 --> 34:07.295
IN AN ACT OF SABOTAGE,

34:02.875 --> 34:07.295
THEN DIED DURING HER ATTEMPT.

34:07.295 --> 34:08.881
SO ANY EVIDENCE SHE'D FOUND

34:08.881 --> 34:12.050
IS TAINTED AS THE WORK

34:08.881 --> 34:12.050
OF A CRAZY PERSON WITH A GRUDGE.

34:12.050 --> 34:15.512
ELIOT, THEY'LL LEAVE HER DOWN

34:12.050 --> 34:15.512
BY THE FERMENTATION TANKS.

34:15.512 --> 34:18.056
YOU KNOW, I SHOULD BE ABLE TO UP

34:15.512 --> 34:18.056
THE OXYGEN LEVELS REMOTELY.

34:18.056 --> 34:19.349
FIRE UP

34:18.056 --> 34:19.349
SOME OF THE AIR MOVERS --

34:19.349 --> 34:21.643
[ BEEPING ]

34:19.349 --> 34:21.643
...OR NOT.

34:21.643 --> 34:23.478
MADIGAN SABOTAGED

34:21.643 --> 34:23.478
THE HVAC SYSTEM.

34:23.478 --> 34:25.063
THE TOWER.

34:25.063 --> 34:27.024
INTERN PARKER LEARNED

34:25.063 --> 34:27.024
ABOUT THE VENTILATION TOWER.

34:27.024 --> 34:29.275
-IF WE CAN GET UP THERE...

34:27.024 --> 34:29.275
-WE CAN OPEN THE DOOR MANUALLY.

34:29.275 --> 34:31.152
OKAY, ELIOT, THE AIR'S

34:29.275 --> 34:31.152
GONNA GET A LITTLE THIN.

34:31.152 --> 34:32.863
WE'RE WORKING ON IT.

34:35.281 --> 34:37.283
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

34:37.283 --> 34:39.786
YO!

34:41.580 --> 34:43.623
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

34:47.753 --> 34:51.130
HOW MUCH TIME DO WE HAVE

34:47.753 --> 34:51.130
BEFORE ELIOT RUNS OUT OF AIR?

34:51.130 --> 34:53.132
THERE THEY ARE! GET THEM!

34:56.720 --> 34:59.848
[ METAL CLANGS ]

34:59.848 --> 35:01.975
[ AIR HISSING ]

35:01.975 --> 35:04.937
[ PANTING ]

35:15.447 --> 35:18.951
Eliot, hold on. We're coming.

35:15.447 --> 35:18.951
Eliot? Eliot?!

35:20.702 --> 35:22.871
THERE THEY ARE! GET THEM!

35:22.871 --> 35:24.122
ELIOT'S RUNNING OUT OF AIR.

35:24.122 --> 35:28.543
[ PANTING ]

35:24.122 --> 35:28.543
LET'S DO THIS.

35:45.769 --> 35:47.813
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

35:50.107 --> 35:54.235
YOUR HEAD'S POUNDING,

35:50.107 --> 35:54.235
YOUR VISION'S STARTING TO GO --

35:54.235 --> 35:56.863
THAT'S YOUR BRAIN

35:54.235 --> 35:56.863
RUNNING OUT OF OXYGEN.

35:56.863 --> 35:59.658
YOU'LL BE UNCONSCIOUS

35:56.863 --> 35:59.658
IN 30 SECONDS.

35:59.658 --> 36:03.244
IT -- IT'LL TAKE ME 10 SECONDS.

36:03.244 --> 36:05.246
[ GRUNTS ]

36:06.581 --> 36:07.916
[ GRUNTS ]

36:07.916 --> 36:09.292
[ AIR HISSING ]

36:19.260 --> 36:20.386
[ GROANING ]

36:20.386 --> 36:23.140
[ SCREAMS ]

36:42.701 --> 36:44.536
[ GROANS ]

36:44.536 --> 36:46.371
Shh, shh, shh.

36:46.371 --> 36:48.790
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

36:52.002 --> 36:54.379
GOOD JOB.

36:54.379 --> 36:57.632
I THINK IT'S ABOUT TIME INTERN

36:54.379 --> 36:57.632
PARKER STARTED GETTING PAID.

36:57.632 --> 36:58.925
[ CHUCKLES ]

36:58.925 --> 37:00.552
[ PANTING ]

37:00.552 --> 37:03.346
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

37:03.346 --> 37:06.516
HEY. HEY.

37:08.560 --> 37:10.269
[ SIGHS ]

37:10.269 --> 37:13.732
YOU ALL RIGHT?

37:13.732 --> 37:17.318
I GOT YOU. COME HERE.

37:20.613 --> 37:24.367
THAT'S IT.

37:20.613 --> 37:24.367
EVERYBODY OUT. WE'RE DONE.

37:29.664 --> 37:31.750
I'D GIVE THAT

37:29.664 --> 37:31.750
A B-PLUS OVERALL.

37:31.750 --> 37:33.626
HAVE WE BEEN WATCHING

37:31.750 --> 37:33.626
THE SAME GAME?

37:33.626 --> 37:34.878
WE BARELY SAVED BETTY.

37:34.878 --> 37:36.379
WE DIDN'T EVEN GET BACK

37:34.878 --> 37:36.379
THE BOTTLE.

37:36.379 --> 37:40.133
WE CONVINCED MADIGAN

37:36.379 --> 37:40.133
THAT THE BOTTLE IS FAKE.

37:40.133 --> 37:41.676
AS FAR AS HE'S CONCERNED,

37:41.676 --> 37:44.387
IT'S ONLY A MATTER OF TIME

37:41.676 --> 37:44.387
BEFORE SOMEONE FINDS OUT.

37:44.387 --> 37:47.766
IT'S A TICKING TIME BOMB

37:44.387 --> 37:47.766
THAT HE HAS TO UNLOAD.

37:47.766 --> 37:50.060
TICK...

37:50.060 --> 37:51.394
TOCK.

37:51.394 --> 37:52.687
TICK...

37:52.687 --> 37:55.481
TOCK.

37:55.481 --> 37:56.816
I'VE BEEN WAITING A LONG TIME

37:56.816 --> 37:58.276
FOR THIS BOTTLE

37:56.816 --> 37:58.276
TO COME ON THE MARKET.

37:58.276 --> 38:00.403
YOU'RE HAPPY

37:58.276 --> 38:00.403
WITH THE AUTHENTICATION?

38:00.403 --> 38:04.323
OH, YEAH. YOUR AUDITOR

38:00.403 --> 38:04.323
WAS VERY CONVINCING.

38:04.323 --> 38:05.951
I JUST, UH, WONDER SOMETHING.

38:05.951 --> 38:08.494
WHY -- WHY DO WE HAVE TO DO THIS

38:05.951 --> 38:08.494
OFF THE BOOKS?

38:08.494 --> 38:10.247
[ CHUCKLES ]

38:10.247 --> 38:12.249
WELL, IT'S NOT THE GOVERNMENT'S

38:10.247 --> 38:12.249
BUSINESS WHERE MY ASSETS GO.

38:12.249 --> 38:14.834
-YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

38:12.249 --> 38:14.834
-SURE, SURE.

38:14.834 --> 38:18.463
I, UH -- I HEARD YOU HAD

38:14.834 --> 38:18.463
TO SHUT DOWN YOUR WINERY.

38:18.463 --> 38:20.715
OH, IT'S JUST A MISUNDERSTANDING

38:18.463 --> 38:20.715
WITH OSHA.

38:20.715 --> 38:22.217
WE'LL CLEAR THAT UP IN NO TIME.

38:22.217 --> 38:24.552
YEAH. WELL...

38:24.552 --> 38:27.597
I COULDN'T BE MORE PLEASED.

38:27.597 --> 38:29.891
IT'S BEEN A PLEASURE.

38:29.891 --> 38:31.684
FRANK MADIGAN?

38:29.891 --> 38:31.684
YOU'RE UNDER ARREST FOR FRAUD.

38:31.684 --> 38:33.478
[ SIREN WAILS, HANDCUFFS CLICK ]

38:33.478 --> 38:34.980
WHAT IS THIS?

38:34.980 --> 38:36.231
WHAT DOES IT LOOK LIKE?

38:34.980 --> 38:36.231
IT'S A STING.

38:36.231 --> 38:37.690
THE AUDITOR THAT YOU BRIBED

38:37.690 --> 38:39.109
CONFESSED TO THIS BOTTLE

38:37.690 --> 38:39.109
FAILING ALL THREE TESTS.

38:39.109 --> 38:40.443
YOU JUST SOLD ME

38:39.109 --> 38:40.443
A FAKE BOTTLE OF WINE

38:40.443 --> 38:42.445
FOR AN AWFUL LOT OF MONEY.

38:42.445 --> 38:45.198
OH, YES. HERE YOU GO.

38:45.198 --> 38:47.408
NO. KEEP IT.

38:45.198 --> 38:47.408
IT'S FAKE, AFTER ALL.

38:47.408 --> 38:49.869
YES. YES.

38:49.869 --> 38:51.746
NO.

38:51.746 --> 38:53.706
NO, IT'S THE REAL BOTTLE.

38:53.706 --> 38:55.792
-NO, THAT'S THE REAL BOTTLE.

38:53.706 --> 38:55.792
-COME ON, LET'S GO. COME ON.

38:55.792 --> 38:59.129
THAT'S THE REAL ONE!

38:55.792 --> 38:59.129
THAT'S THE  REAL  ONE!!

38:59.129 --> 39:01.965
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

39:04.009 --> 39:06.303
OKAY, IN HERE IS EVERYTHING

39:04.009 --> 39:06.303
YOU WILL NEED TO BUILD A CASE

39:06.303 --> 39:08.305
AGAINST FRANK MADIGAN

39:06.303 --> 39:08.305
AND HIS FOREMAN.

39:08.305 --> 39:10.015
EVERYTHING.

39:10.015 --> 39:12.809
THANK YOU. FOR EVERYTHING.

39:12.809 --> 39:14.727
WELL, SHE GOT THERE FIRST.

39:14.727 --> 39:17.814
YOUR FATHER WAS A GOOD MAN.

39:19.649 --> 39:21.526
THE MONEY YOU GAVE US --

39:21.526 --> 39:23.945
IT WAS ENOUGH TO BUY BACK

39:21.526 --> 39:23.945
THE WINERY.

39:23.945 --> 39:26.489
WE ARE NOW 100% EMPLOYEE-OWNED.

39:26.489 --> 39:30.076
WE CAN'T THANK YOU ENOUGH.

39:30.076 --> 39:33.246
JUST TAKE GOOD CARE

39:30.076 --> 39:33.246
OF THE PLACE.

39:41.046 --> 39:43.048
HELLO, BEAUTIFUL.

39:43.048 --> 39:45.050
THE MONEY YOU GAVE THEM.

39:45.050 --> 39:48.928
OH, I MAY HAVE FOUND A BUYER

39:45.050 --> 39:48.928
FOR THE JEFFERSON BOTTLE.

39:48.928 --> 39:51.097
OH. OH.

39:51.097 --> 39:52.349
HMM.

39:52.349 --> 39:55.352
EW. IT'S NOT HARDISON'S BREW,

39:52.349 --> 39:55.352
IS IT?

39:55.352 --> 39:58.437
OH, NO. CERTAINLY NOT.

39:55.352 --> 39:58.437
[ CHUCKLES ]

39:58.437 --> 40:00.899
IN MEMORY OF KRISTIN'S FATHER...

40:00.899 --> 40:03.193
AND IN HONOR OF GOOD FRIENDS.

40:03.193 --> 40:04.361
MM.

40:04.361 --> 40:07.446
AND WITH HOPE FOR THE FUTURE.

40:07.446 --> 40:10.158
HMM.

40:14.329 --> 40:15.663
WOW.

40:15.663 --> 40:16.831
THAT'S AMAZING.

40:16.831 --> 40:17.790
AHH.

40:17.790 --> 40:20.126
-IT TASTES..

40:17.790 --> 40:20.126
-SPECIAL.

40:23.004 --> 40:24.714
UH...

40:24.714 --> 40:26.925
[ GASPS ]

40:26.925 --> 40:30.011
YOU SAID YOU FOUND A BUYER

40:26.925 --> 40:30.011
FOR THE BOTTLE.

40:30.011 --> 40:31.137
YOU DIDN'T SAY "WINE."

40:31.137 --> 40:32.889
YOU SAID

40:31.137 --> 40:32.889
"THE JEFFERSON  BOTTLE."

40:32.889 --> 40:34.349
OH, I MEANT WINE

40:32.889 --> 40:34.349
WHEN I SAID BOTTLE.

40:34.349 --> 40:36.268
I MEAN, IT'S NOT LIKE

40:34.349 --> 40:36.268
THE NEXT BUYER

40:36.268 --> 40:38.561
IS EVER GOING TO

40:36.268 --> 40:38.561
TASTE THE WINE.

40:38.561 --> 40:39.979
IT'S TOO VALUABLE.

40:39.979 --> 40:42.774
NO, OF COURSE I MEANT

40:39.979 --> 40:42.774
[CLEARS THROAT] WINE.

40:42.774 --> 40:46.652
YOU MEAN...WE...

40:42.774 --> 40:46.652
ARE DRINKING

40:46.652 --> 40:49.239
THE WORLD'S MOST EXPENSIVE WINE?

40:49.239 --> 40:51.324
YOU'RE THE WINE EXPERT.

40:51.324 --> 40:55.494
AND YOU'RE NEVER GONNA TELL ME,

40:51.324 --> 40:55.494
ARE YOU?

40:55.494 --> 40:57.830
[ SIGHS ]

40:57.830 --> 40:59.416
I DO KNOW THE DIFFERENCE

40:59.416 --> 41:02.961
BETWEEN WHAT'S REAL

40:59.416 --> 41:02.961
AND WHAT'S FAKE.

41:04.296 --> 41:05.588
[ GLASSES CLINK ]

